******
[2] California (Tehama County)
Date: Thu 27 Mar 2014
Source: KRCR TV [edited]
http://m.krcrtv.com/confirmed-whooping-cough-case-in-tehama-county/25204144


Tehama County Public Health revealed today [27 Mar 2014] that they've had a confirmed case of pertussis, also known as whooping cough, so they're reminding people to take precautions. They recommend that adults who have not had a vaccination get one. Infants are at higher risk and should be vaccinated at 2 months of age.

Pregnant women and also family members who are around infants should get vaccinated, since the bacterial disease is spread through talking, sneezing or coughing.

Linda Rose, Tehama County Health supervising nurse, said it's also important to keep an eye out for symptoms.

[Byline: Stephanie Montano]

